2009-07-24  Guillaume-Jean Herbiet <Guillaume.Herbiet@uni.lu>
	* Fixed bug with sparsebundle target: default mountpoint "Backup_Sparsebundle" was used which caused creation of simlink "latest" that was broken when mounting the sparsebundle manually if the sparsebundle name differed from "Backup_Sparsebundle".
	* Experimental implementation of backup history : - Each backup creates a timestamped directory in the specified target where files are backuped. To limit disk usage, unchanged files are hard linked with existing version on target. - Up-to-date snapshot is always available under the "latest" directory. - (Not yet supported)   Backup with history over SSH, causes a backup failure - (Not yet implemented) Behavior on target disk full - (Not yet implemented) History consolidation - (Not yet implemented) Retrieve mode from latest snapshot, causes a retrieve failure
	* - Modified sparsebundle protocol error messages to be more consistant with other protocols - Updated TODO to reflect recent modifications

2009-07-23  Guillaume-Jean Herbiet <Guillaume.Herbiet@uni.lu>
	* - Added support for rsync with Mac OS resource forks (extended attributes), see -m option - Added support for pre/post backup scripts, see --pre-backup and --post-backup options - Added support for sparsebundle images through the sparsebundle:/// protocol - Added user notification (Growl under Mac OS X, notify-send under Linux), see the --notification option

